main event: A witness reported observing a fast-moving object with yellowish-green light near Ada, Minnesota on April 5, 1952.
interesting points: The object was initially circular and changed to an oval shape, The object split into two parts before disappearing horizontally, Witness estimated the object's speed at 300 to 500 mph, The object traveled from North to South at an altitude of 150 to 200 feet, No trail, smoke, or noise was observed.
sighted object: yellowish-green light emitted from a fast moving object
witness description: Witness provided a detailed account of the sighting including speed, size, and movement.
